cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) using attentional mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also discusses different architectures for attention-based NMT, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions using attention to focus on specific parts of the source sentence, which could relate to computer vision tasks, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category as well.
